    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but what about the strain on local infrastructure and the wage suppression for low-skilled workers? even if gdp goes up, doesn't that mean the benefits are being concentrated and certain groups are actually being hurt economically? it doesn't feel like one of those things can be \"settled\" if people are feeling the impact in their own pockets.",
