      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While some localized strains on infrastructure can occur, these are manageable logistical challenges, not fundamental economic flaws of immigration itself. The argument about wage suppression is often overstated; studies show that the impact on the wages of native-born low-skilled workers is minimal, especially when considering the overall economic growth spurred by the newcomers. Ultimately, the benefits of a larger, more dynamic labor force and increased consumption outweigh these localized concerns.",
